article.headline: Wagner 80, Sacred Heart 76
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Ulrich had a career-high 24 points and 10 rebounds for his fourth career triple-double as Wagner held off Sacred Heart 80-76 on Monday night. Mark Porter added 16 points, Jamal Smith had 12 and Matt Vitale 10 for the Seahawks (9-13, 6-5 Northeast). Chauncey Hardy shot 4-of-7 from 3-point range and led the Pioneers (11-11, 7-4) with 16 points. Joey Henley, Jarrid Frye and Drew Shubik each had 12 points. Shubick had four points as Sacred Heart took a 6-0 lead, but Wagner went on a 20-3 run to take command 20-9 at 11:22 of the opening half. Ullrich had 10 points during the run, capped by a jumper. Sacred Heart scored nine unanswered points to get as close as 20-18 on a pair of foul shots by Shubik, and trailed 41-35 at halftime.
